name: Starbucks
directions: Restrooms are located in the back of the cafe and require a passcode.
comment: I always default to using Starbucks restrooms because they are gender neutral and single occupant. In my experience, with restrooms requiring a passcode, politely asking the Barista’s seems to be the trick. I’ve seen too many people turned away with the “you have to make a purchase” simply because they stormed in and asked what the passcode was for the restrooms. Just be nice when you ask if you don’t plan on making a purchase, and I’m sure the Barista will give you access.

One of the most queer friendly breweries we’ve ever been to! Awesome staff, great beer, clean bathrooms. 2 single occupancy bathrooms, urinal in the one on the left, changing table in the one on the right. Both stocked with tampons and pads. 
Super dog friendly too! They even have a stack of dog beds & bowls by the door!
